Sometimes that 12% beer just won&rsquo;t cut it. Legislation in the Ohio House would allow beer to be produced in Ohio with up to 21% alcohol. The legislation is designed for microbreweries in the state who are looking to compete with breweries in other states who are allowed to brew higher than 12%. Fewer than ten states nationwide limit the ABV in beer.
